Linux Fundamentals

1. What is Linux?

Linux is an Operating System (like Windows) but:
	•	Free & Open Source
	•	Very fast & secure
	•	Used on servers, cloud, Docker, Kubernetes

90% of DevOps tools run on Linux

2. Linux Architecture (Easy)

User
 ↓
Shell (Terminal)
 ↓
Kernel (Brain of Linux)
 ↓
Hardware

    •	Kernel → Talks to hardware
	•	Shell → Where we type commands
	•	Terminal → Black screen

3. Linux File System Structure

Everything starts from / (root)

Directory          Use
/                  Root
/home              User folders
/etc               Configuration files
/var               Logs, variable data
/bin               Basic commands
/usr               User software
/tmp               Temporary files

